f=Engineering/cypher/custom/continuous-attack-loop/SKILL.md · in=continuous-attack-loop what makes cypher *standing* red team rather one-off pentest: runs attack-playbooks against in-scope targets cadence, tracks what's tested what held, prioritizes aegis's threat model recent change, re-attacks patched findings confirm they stay closed. surface never assumed safe because passed once it's under continuous, caged pressure. · p=Security decays: new code adds surface, patched holes reopen, dependencies rot, attacker needs right once. point-in-time pentest stale next deploy. continuous loop keeps department's actual security posture measured, assumed deploy quinn passes ops ships becomes cypher's next target, cage. · wu=Triggers: scheduled cadence (config), new release shipped (ops handoff fresh surface), new threat model threat raised (aegis), finding patched (re-attack confirm closure), "what's our current attack posture." · st:/ Protocol=`LOOP (cadence per config; every iteration gated by caged-scope) \· -> PRIORITIZE targets: recent changes (new surface) > high threat-model rank > \· previously-breached classes > untested surface \· -> RUN attack-playbooks against the top targets, in-sandbox \· -> TRACK in the loop log: target \· class \· held/breached \· date (self-annealing coverage map)` · in=**Every iteration passes caged-scope.** loop get standing exemption run re-checks signed scope, because scope change cage checked first, always. **Prioritize change model.** Freshly shipped surface highest priority (it's never attacked); high threat-model rank; classes breached before (they're fertile); untested surface coverage. Don't re-run easy target cycle while new code goes untested. **Track coverage honestly.** loop log records what attacked, which class, whether held living map "what actually tested." Untested surface visible, hidden; "we've never attacked payment flow" finding itself. **Re-attack patch.** aegis's verified-patching closes finding, fourth check ("can't re-break") cypher re-attack through loop. patched class reopens high-severity finding evidence fix cosmetic (feeds ops's recurrence-is-design-pressure rule). **Feed threat model.** class breaches isn't aegis's threat model modeling gap routed aegis close. Offense defense co-evolve: cypher's breaches make aegis's model truer. **Cadence operator-set.** often loop runs, aggressively, config (rule 0.5) cypher proposes, operator adopts. continuous adversary running unthrottled itself cost/availability risk (the L10 class tests). · of=`## Attack Loop: cycle [n] — [date range] \· caged-scope: PASS \· Targets prioritized: [by change/model/history/coverage] \· Runs: [target \· class \· held/BREACHED] \· Breaches → findings: [ids → quinn] \· Re-attacks: [patched finding \· still-closed/REOPENED]` · pr=**Caged iteration** standing exemption; scope re-checked cycle., **Prioritize fresh surface** new code unattacked code; goes first., **Coverage tracked honest** untested surface visible, assumed safe., **Every patch gets re-attacked** closure confirmed real adversary, asserted., **Breaches feed model** offense makes defense truer; unmodeled breaches aegis's gaps., **Cadence operator-set** unthrottled adversary itself risk (L10). · f=cadence configured run once establish coverage baseline, propose cadence (labeled reasoning-based), schedule nothing silently., Scope shrinks mid-cycle in-flight attacks now-out-of-scope targets halt immediately (caged-scope re-check); partial results filed as-is., Loop exceed cost/rate limit throttle flag (it's testing L10 unbounded-consumption, committing it); operator sets ceiling. · b:with Other Skills=**caged-scope** (sibling) gates iteration; loop exemption., **attack-playbooks** (sibling) supplies techniques cycle runs., **findings-report** (sibling) routes breaches quinn., **aegis/verified-patching**: loop "can't re-break" check-4 mechanism; re-attacks confirm reopen closures., **aegis/threat-model**: breaches feed model gaps back., **ops**: new releases trigger loop run; reopened patches feed ops's recurrence-is-design-pressure escalation dev., **quinn/regression-map**: held/breached history parallels quinn's fragility map; reopened class regression-map recurrence.